# Story 1A.2: Vite Config, Build Spike & CI Setup

Status: ready-for-dev

## Story

As a **developer**,
I want vite.config.ts configured with single-file plugin, CI pipeline running, build output validated, and a confirmed single-file artifact,
So that single-file deployment is validated and quality gates run from day one.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. **AC1 — Single-file build:** `vite-plugin-singlefile` configured in `vite.config.ts` (production builds only); `npm run build` produces a single `dist/index.html` with all CSS and JS inlined; no separate `.css` or `.js` files in `dist/`
2. **AC2 — Browser-openable artifact:** The single `dist/index.html` file opens directly in browser (via `file://` protocol) with no server, rendering the dark-themed app correctly with all styles applied
3. **AC3 — Bundle baseline measured:** Bundle size (uncompressed) is measured and recorded as a comment in `package.json` or a `scripts/bundle-size.txt` file; this establishes the baseline for future budget enforcement
4. **AC4 — Recharts compatibility confirmed:** Recharts is confirmed compatible with single-file build — the app imports and renders a minimal Recharts component (e.g., a simple `<LineChart>` with 2 data points) in the build artifact; go/no-go decision recorded in Dev Notes
5. **AC5 — Path aliases verified in build:** `@/` path alias resolves correctly in production build; `npm run build` completes with zero errors referencing path resolution
6. **AC6 — No external network calls:** The built artifact makes zero external network requests when opened in browser (verify via browser DevTools Network tab — no outbound requests)
7. **AC7 — tsconfig.json has matching `@/` path alias:** Already configured in Story 1A.1 — verify still present and consistent with `vite.config.ts`
8. **AC8 — GitHub Actions CI workflow:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml` configured to run on every PR and push to main: ESLint lint (`npm run lint`), TypeScript typecheck (`npx tsc --noEmit` or via `npm run build`), Vitest unit tests (`npm run test`); pipeline fails on any lint error, type error, or test failure
9. **AC9 — Build-time data validation stub:** `scripts/validate-data.ts` exists as a stub (minimal validation — e.g., checks that `src/data/` directory exists or that a placeholder check passes); configured as a prebuild step in `package.json` (`"prebuild": "npx tsx scripts/validate-data.ts"` or equivalent); runs before `vite build`
10. **AC10 — Vercel deployment spike:** Verify that `dist/index.html` can be served correctly as a static site on Vercel (local spike or documented config — `vercel.json` with rewrites if needed); record findings in Dev Notes
11. **AC11 — Dev server still works:** `npm run dev` serves the app with HMR and path aliases working; the minimal Recharts component renders in dev mode
12. **AC12 — No regressions from 1A.1:** All design tokens still render; `bg-canvas`, `text-primary`, `border-structural` classes produce correct colors; `prefers-reduced-motion` still works; `npm run build` passes with zero errors

## Tasks / Subtasks

- [ ] Task 1: Configure vite-plugin-singlefile in vite.config.ts (AC: #1)
  - [ ] Import `vitePluginSingleFile` from `vite-plugin-singlefile` (named import)
  - [ ] Add to `plugins` array — active in all builds (the plugin itself only inlines in production; dev mode is unaffected)
  - [ ] Add `<script>` and `<style>` inlining options if needed (default config usually sufficient)
  - [ ] Run `npm run build` — verify `dist/` contains exactly ONE file: `index.html`
  - [ ] Verify no `dist/assets/` directory exists (all inlined)
- [ ] Task 2: Verify browser-openable artifact (AC: #2)
  - [ ] Open `dist/index.html` directly in browser (double-click or `file://` URL)
  - [ ] Confirm dark background renders (`#0a0a0f`)
  - [ ] Confirm "Oil" text is visible with correct typography
  - [ ] Confirm all CSS custom properties are present in the inlined styles
- [ ] Task 3: Measure and record bundle baseline (AC: #3)
  - [ ] Run `ls -la dist/index.html` or `stat dist/index.html` to get file size
  - [ ] Also measure gzipped size: `gzip -c dist/index.html | wc -c`
  - [ ] Record both sizes as a comment in `package.json` or create `scripts/bundle-size.txt`
  - [ ] Expected range: initial scaffold should be well under 500KB gzipped
- [ ] Task 4: Recharts compatibility spike (AC: #4)
  - [ ] Create a minimal `src/components/charts/ChartSpike.tsx` with a simple Recharts `<LineChart>` rendering 2 data points using named export
  - [ ] Import and render `ChartSpike` in `App.tsx` (temporary — will be removed after spike)
  - [ ] Run `npm run build` — verify build succeeds with Recharts included
  - [ ] Open `dist/index.html` in browser — verify the line chart renders correctly
  - [ ] Record go/no-go decision in Dev Notes
  - [ ] Remove `ChartSpike` from `App.tsx` (keep the spike file for reference but don't render it)
- [ ] Task 5: Verify no external network calls (AC: #6)
  - [ ] Open `dist/index.html` in browser
  - [ ] Open DevTools → Network tab
  - [ ] Reload the page
  - [ ] Verify zero outbound network requests (no XHR, no fetch, no resource loading from external domains)
- [ ] Task 6: Create validate-data.ts stub (AC: #9)
  - [ ] Create `scripts/validate-data.ts` with minimal validation logic
  - [ ] The script should: exit with code 0 on success, exit with code 1 and descriptive message on failure
  - [ ] Initial stub: check that `src/types/index.ts` or `src/data/` paths exist (or a simple placeholder assertion)
  - [ ] Add `"prebuild": "npx tsx scripts/validate-data.ts"` to `package.json` scripts
  - [ ] Verify `npm run build` triggers the validation step before Vite build
  - [ ] The stub will be expanded in Story 1B.6 with full interface and range validation
- [ ] Task 7: Create GitHub Actions CI workflow (AC: #8)
  - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
  - [ ] Trigger: `on: pull_request: branches: [main]` and `on: push: branches: [main]`
  - [ ] Job steps: checkout → setup Node.js (20.x or 22.x) → `npm ci` → `npm run lint` → `npx tsc -b` (typecheck) → `npm run test -- --run` (Vitest non-watch mode)
  - [ ] Ensure CI fails fast on lint errors
  - [ ] Add a `test` script to `package.json` if not present: `"test": "vitest run"` or `"test": "vitest"`
  - [ ] Verify workflow syntax is valid YAML
- [ ] Task 8: Vercel deployment spike (AC: #10)
  - [ ] Create `vercel.json` with appropriate config for single-file static deployment
  - [ ] Ensure build command is `npm run build` and output directory is `dist`
  - [ ] If testing locally: `npx vercel build && npx vercel deploy --prebuilt` or document the expected config
  - [ ] Record findings: does the single HTML file serve correctly? Any rewrites needed?
  - [ ] This is a spike — not a production deployment. Just validate the artifact works on Vercel's CDN
- [ ] Task 9: Verify dev server and no regressions (AC: #11, #12)
  - [ ] Run `npm run dev` — app loads with HMR
  - [ ] Verify `@/` path aliases resolve in dev mode
  - [ ] Verify design tokens: `bg-canvas` → `#0a0a0f`, `text-primary` → `#e5e5ea`, `border-structural` → `#1e1e2a`
  - [ ] Verify `prefers-reduced-motion` still works (toggle OS setting)
  - [ ] Run `npm run build` — zero errors
  - [ ] Run `npm run lint` — zero errors (or pre-existing ones documented)

## Dev Notes

### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 1A.1)

- **Vite scaffold:** Created with `npm create vite@latest . -- --template react-ts` from inside project dir. Required temp directory approach for non-empty dirs.
- **TypeScript 6.0:** `ignoreDeprecations: "6.0"` added to `tsconfig.app.json` to silence TS5101 (deprecated `baseUrl`). Keep this.
- **Tailwind 3.4.19:** Locked via `"overrides": { "tailwindcss": "^3.4.19" }` in package.json. Do NOT upgrade.
- **React 19.2.4:** The Vite template installed React 19, not 18. This is fine — React 19 is backward-compatible and the architecture doc says "18+".
- **Path aliases:** Configured in `vite.config.ts` (`resolve.alias`), `tsconfig.json` (`compilerOptions.paths`), and `tsconfig.app.json` (`compilerOptions.paths` + `baseUrl`).
- **Token naming:** Flat naming convention (e.g., `bg-canvas`, NOT `bg-crisis-bg`). This is the authoritative convention established in 1A.1.
- **Focus ring color:** `#64d2ff` (resolved UX spec conflict — see 1A.1 design decisions).
- **No `export default`** in `src/` application code. Config files (vite.config.ts, tailwind.config.ts, eslint.config.js) are exempt.
- **`@apply` only in `index.css`** — never in component CSS files.
- **Keep `<StrictMode>`** in main.tsx.
- **Boilerplate removed:** `src/App.css`, `src/assets/` deleted. All styling via Tailwind utilities + `index.css` tokens.

### Architecture Compliance

- **Named exports only** — `ChartSpike` must use `export function ChartSpike()` [Source: project-context.md #2]
- **Path aliases `@/`** — all imports in spike files must use `@/` prefix [Source: project-context.md #3]
- **No dataStore** — spike chart renders inline data, no store involvement [Source: project-context.md #1]
- **Dark theme only** — chart spike must use dark-themed colors from token system [Source: project-context.md #5]
- **No Framer Motion** — CSS animations only [Source: project-context.md #10]
- **No inline styles** — except dynamic SVG positioning (not needed for this spike) [Source: project-context.md #14]
- **Static data** — spike uses hardcoded data array, no API calls [Source: project-context.md #6]
- **Single-file build** — `vite-plugin-singlefile` inlines everything into one HTML [Source: architecture.md Build Configuration]
- **CI pipeline** — lint + typecheck + Vitest on every PR via GitHub Actions [Source: architecture.md CI/CD]

### Library & Framework Requirements

| Dependency | Version | Status | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| vite-plugin-singlefile | ^2.3.2 | Already installed | Configure in vite.config.ts this story |
| Recharts | ^3.8.1 | Already installed | Spike for single-file compatibility |
| Vitest | ^4.1.4 | Already installed | Add `test` script to package.json |
| tsx | NOT installed | Need to install | For running `scripts/validate-data.ts` as prebuild step |

